description:
Wire the Agent's run loop to actually invoke tools. When the streaming model emits ToolUseComplete events, the Agent dispatches each tool via its registry, appends ToolCall and ToolResult Blocks to History, and re-enters the model loop until the model produces a response with no tool calls. This is the control-flow centerpiece of Phase 2.

Architectural shape (per ARCHITECTURE.md §Agent):
- Outer loop: per inbound Block. Each inbound block triggers ONE OR MORE model calls.
- Inner loop ("tool-call cycle"): until the model produces a response with zero tool calls.
- Each model call emits a RunComplete event. Subscribers see a sequence of RunCompletes per inbound message; the final one signals "agent idle".
- AgentMessage Block is still appended after every model call that produced any text content. If the model produced ONLY tool calls (no text), no AgentMessage is appended for that iteration. This avoids polluting History with empty AgentMessage blocks.

Scope:

1. src/test_support.rs -- extend StubArModel for multi-call test scripts:

The current StubArModel takes a single `Vec<Result<...>>` and `mem::take`s it on first call, so a second call returns an empty stream. For bd-7b tests we need to script multiple calls.

Refactor `StubArModel::with_events` to accept `Vec<Vec<Result<ModelStreamEvent, model::Error>>>` (one script per expected call). Keep `last_input` semantics (always captures the LAST input). On each `complete()` call, pop the front script and emit it as a stream; if the queue is empty, return an empty stream.

Also keep the existing single-script convenience: rename the existing `with_events` to `with_call_scripts` (multi-call) AND retain a `with_events(single_script)` shim that wraps a single Vec in `vec![single_script]` so existing tests continue to compile unchanged. Same for `empty()` (returns no scripts).

Reformulated API:
```rust
impl StubArModel {
    pub fn with_call_scripts(scripts: Vec<Vec<Result<ModelStreamEvent, model::Error>>>) -> Self { ... }
    pub fn with_events(events: Vec<Result<ModelStreamEvent, model::Error>>) -> Self {
        Self::with_call_scripts(vec![events])
    }
    pub fn empty() -> Self {
        Self::with_call_scripts(Vec::new())
    }
}
```

Internal state: `Mutex<VecDeque<Vec<Result<...>>>>` or `Mutex<Vec<...>>` with pop_front via `remove(0)`. The `complete()` impl pops one script per call.

2. src/agent.rs -- rewire Agent::run:

a. Replace the existing single inner model-call sequence with a tool-call cycle. Pseudocode:

```rust
while let Some(block) = self.inbound.next().await {
    let inbound_node = self.history.append(block);
    let _ = self.bus.publish(self.id, AgentEvent::BlockComplete { block: inbound_node });

    loop {  // tool-call cycle
        let context = self.history.linearize();
        let tools = self.tools.list().into_iter().map(|t| ToolSpec { ... }).collect();
        let turns = compile_turns(&self.system_prompt, context);
        let input = ModelInput { turns, tools };

        let model = self.models.get(&ModelRole::Default).ok_or(...)?.clone();
        let mut stream = model.complete(&input);

        let mut delta_buffer = String::new();
        let mut completed_text: Option<String> = None;
        let mut final_usage = Usage::default();
        let mut pending_tool_calls: Vec<(String, String, serde_json::Value)> = Vec::new();

        while let Some(evt) = stream.next().await {
            match evt? {
                ModelStreamEvent::ContentDelta { text } => { delta_buffer.push_str(&text); publish TokenDelta }
                ModelStreamEvent::ContentComplete { text } => { completed_text = Some(text); }
                ModelStreamEvent::Usage(u) => { final_usage = u; }
                ModelStreamEvent::MessageComplete { usage } => { final_usage = usage; }
                ModelStreamEvent::MessageStart { .. } => {}
                ModelStreamEvent::Error { .. } => {}
                ModelStreamEvent::ToolUseStart { .. } => {} // start/delta are observation-only; we only need Complete for dispatch
                ModelStreamEvent::ToolUseDelta { .. } => {}
                ModelStreamEvent::ToolUseComplete { id, name, input } => {
                    pending_tool_calls.push((id, name, input));
                }
            }
        }
        drop(stream);

        // Decide whether to append AgentMessage. Only if there was any text content.
        let text_content = completed_text.unwrap_or(delta_buffer);
        if !text_content.is_empty() {
            let agent_msg_node = self.history.append(Block::AgentMessage {
                from: self.id,
                content: text_content,
                timestamp: SystemTime::now(),
            });
            let _ = self.bus.publish(self.id, AgentEvent::BlockComplete { block: agent_msg_node });
        }

        let _ = self.bus.publish(self.id, AgentEvent::RunComplete { usage: final_usage });

        if pending_tool_calls.is_empty() {
            break; // model produced no tool calls; cycle done
        }

        // Dispatch each pending tool call sequentially. For each:
        //   - append Block::ToolCall, publish BlockComplete
        //   - dispatch via registry
        //   - append Block::ToolResult (is_error=false on Ok, true on Err), publish BlockComplete
        for (id, name, args) in pending_tool_calls {
            let call_node = self.history.append(Block::ToolCall {
                id: id.clone(),
                name: name.clone(),
                arguments: args.clone(),
                timestamp: SystemTime::now(),
            });
            let _ = self.bus.publish(self.id, AgentEvent::BlockComplete { block: call_node });

            let (result_json, is_error) = match self.tools.dispatch(&name, args).await {
                Ok(value) => (value, false),
                Err(err) => (serde_json::json!({"error": err.to_string()}), true),
            };

            let result_node = self.history.append(Block::ToolResult {
                tool_use_id: id,
                name,
                result: result_json,
                is_error,
                timestamp: SystemTime::now(),
            });
            let _ = self.bus.publish(self.id, AgentEvent::BlockComplete { block: result_node });
        }
        // loop back: re-enter the model loop with extended history
    }
}
```

Notes:
- The existing no-op match arm for ToolUseStart|Delta|Complete is REMOVED and replaced with three separate arms above (Start and Delta are no-ops in this bead -- they exist only so the parser surface is exhaustive).
- ToolError -> serialized as `{"error": "<message>"}` JSON. This is what the model will see in the next iteration as Block::ToolResult.result.
- `text_content.is_empty()` check ensures no empty AgentMessage Blocks pollute History when the model produces only tool calls.

b. Helper extraction is OPTIONAL: if the History-to-Turns compilation block gets re-used inside the loop, you may extract it into a private `fn compile_turns(system_prompt: &str, context: Vec<Block>) -> Vec<Turn>`. Do NOT export it. Tests do not require it.

