## `src/agent.rs` — Agent loses its channel fields
Current shape:
```rust
pub struct Agent {
    id: AgentId,
    system_prompt: String,
    models: HashMap<ModelRole, Arc<dyn ARModel>>,
    history: History,
    inbound: mpsc::Receiver<Block>,
    outbound: broadcast::Sender<AgentEvent>,
}
```

New shape:
```rust
pub struct Agent {
    id: AgentId,
    system_prompt: String,
    models: HashMap<ModelRole, Arc<dyn ARModel>>,
    history: History,
    inbound: futures::stream::BoxStream<'static, Block>,
    bus: std::sync::Arc<dyn crate::messagebus::MessageBus>,
}
```

The `AgentBuilder::build` signature changes from
```rust
fn build(self, inbound: mpsc::Receiver<Block>, outbound: broadcast::Sender<AgentEvent>) -> Result<Agent, Error>;
```
to
```rust
fn build(self, bus: Arc<dyn MessageBus>) -> Result<Agent, Error>;
```

Inside `build`, after validating `id`/`system_prompt`/`ModelRole::Default`, call `bus.register(id)?` and store the returned `BoxStream<Block>` as `Agent::inbound`. Map `messagebus::Error` via a new `From` impl on `agent::Error`:
```rust
impl From<crate::messagebus::Error> for Error {
    fn from(e: crate::messagebus::Error) -> Self {
        Error::Bus(e)
    }
}
```
Add a new variant `agent::Error::Bus(crate::messagebus::Error)` with `Display`/`source()` updates.

`Agent::run` event loop changes:
- Replace `while let Some(block) = self.inbound.recv().await` with `while let Some(block) = self.inbound.next().await` (use `futures::StreamExt`).
- Replace every `let _ = self.outbound.send(event);` with `let _ = self.bus.publish(self.id, event);`.
- Otherwise the loop body is unchanged.

## `src/harness.rs` — wire the new bus-mediated Agent
- `Harness::start`'s per-agent body simplifies. The Harness no longer calls `bus.register` directly; that happens inside `AgentBuilder::build`. The Harness still needs to know the agent failed, so it keeps an `Arc<dyn MessageBus>` clone to publish `AgentEvent::Error` after the spawned task exits with `Err`. Pseudocode (the only function being modified is `start`):
  ```rust
  for spec in pending {
      let model = self.models.get(&spec.model_id)
          .ok_or_else(|| Error::UnknownModel(spec.model_id.clone()))?
          .clone();
      let agent = AgentBuilder::new()
          .id(spec.id)
          .system_prompt(spec.system_prompt.clone())
          .model(ModelRole::Default, model)
          .build(self.bus.clone() as Arc<dyn MessageBus>)?;
      let bus_for_emit = self.bus.clone();
      let cancel_for_task = self.cancel.clone();
      let agent_id = spec.id;
      let task = tokio::spawn(async move {
          let res = tokio::select! {
              _ = cancel_for_task.cancelled() => Ok::<(), Error>(()),
              res = agent.run() => res.map_err(Error::from),
          };
          if let Err(ref e) = res {
              let _ = bus_for_emit.publish(agent_id, AgentEvent::Error { message: e.to_string() });
          }
          res
      });
      self.agents.insert(agent_id, AgentHandle { task });
  }
  ```
- `AgentHandle` simplifies — it no longer needs to hold the outbound `Sender` clone (it was used by the prior `Harness::subscribe` fast-path; the fast-path is replaced with `self.bus.subscribe(agent_id)`).
- `Harness::subscribe(&self, agent_id)` becomes a thin wrapper that calls `self.bus.subscribe(agent_id)` and adapts the error type via `From<messagebus::Error>` on `harness::Error`. The return type CHANGES from `Result<broadcast::Receiver<AgentEvent>, Error>` to `Result<futures::stream::BoxStream<'static, AgentEvent>, Error>`. Update `src/lib.rs::run_async` callers accordingly (see §`src/lib.rs` below).
- `Harness::send_to_agent` is unchanged in shape: calls `self.bus.send_inbound(...)`.
- The `#[cfg(test)] pub fn bus()` accessor stays for now (the test that uses it will be re-pointed to the new API; if removing the accessor is trivial after the test rewrite, do so — otherwise leave it).

## `src/lib.rs::run_async` — subscriber type changes from `broadcast::Receiver` to `BoxStream`
The recv loop currently uses `rx.recv().await` with `Result<AgentEvent, broadcast::error::RecvError>`. With `BoxStream<AgentEvent>` it becomes `rx.next().await -> Option<AgentEvent>`. Adjust the match accordingly:
```rust
use futures::StreamExt;
let mut rx = harness.subscribe(agent_id)?;
// ...
while runs_completed < 2 {
    match rx.next().await {
        Some(AgentEvent::TokenDelta { text }) => { print!("{text}"); std::io::stdout().flush()?; }
        Some(AgentEvent::RunComplete { usage }) => {
            println!();
            eprintln!("[usage: input_tokens={} output_tokens={}]", usage.input_tokens, usage.output_tokens);
            runs_completed += 1;
            if !second_sent {
                harness.send_to_agent(agent_id, owner_id, SECOND_MESSAGE.into())?;
                second_sent = true;
            }
        }
        Some(AgentEvent::Error { message }) => return Err(anyhow::anyhow!("agent error: {message}")),
        Some(AgentEvent::BlockComplete { .. }) => {}
        None => break,
    }
}
```
The `Lagged` arm goes away because we filter Lagged at the stream level inside `InMemoryMessageBus::subscribe`. The `Closed` arm is replaced by `None`.

