### 2. Tmp dir initialization (per-process)

Use `std::sync::OnceLock<PathBuf>` (or equivalent — `tokio::sync::OnceCell` is fine too if you prefer async init; `OnceLock` is std and sync-init-friendly):

```rust
use std::path::PathBuf;
use std::sync::OnceLock;

static TMP_DIR: OnceLock<PathBuf> = OnceLock::new();

fn ensure_tmp_dir() -> Result<&'static PathBuf, ExecBashError> {
    if let Some(dir) = TMP_DIR.get() {
        return Ok(dir);
    }
    let pid = std::process::id();
    let dir = std::env::temp_dir().join(format!("pristine-{pid}"));
    std::fs::create_dir_all(&dir)
        .map_err(|e| ExecBashError::TmpFile { reason: format!("create_dir_all: {e}") })?;
    // OnceLock::set returns Err if already set by a racing thread; in that case we just use the existing value.
    let _ = TMP_DIR.set(dir);
    let stored = TMP_DIR.get()
        .ok_or_else(|| ExecBashError::TmpFile { reason: "OnceLock unexpectedly empty".to_string() })?;
    Ok(stored)
}
```

**Cleanup at harness shutdown** is OUT OF SCOPE for this bead. The plan defers it; we'll leak the directory until shutdown logic is wired through the harness in a future cycle. Add an `// TODO: cleanup at shutdown (see PLAN.md "ExecBash tmp files" decision)` comment ONLY at the relevant tmp-dir-creation site so the deferral is documented in the code.

