## Plan-respect note

`EditError` is the dialect: tool-specific variants (MultipleMatches, NoMatches, NotUtf8). The `err` helper bridges to the portable carrier `ToolError::Execution(Value)`. Path resolution stays inline — promotion to a cross-tool helper happens only when at least two consumers actually share the pattern (the plan's promotion rule).

## Goal
The conceptual integrity review and subsequent design discussion concluded that the `Model` trait should not see `Block`. `Block` is the History's vocabulary (a durable event log); the Model's input is a separate, narrower contract. Introduce a structured `ModelInput` type that the Agent constructs and the Model consumes. Adapters map `ModelInput` to their provider-native shape; the conversion that currently lives inside `AnthropicModel::block_to_message` (silently dropping three Block variants) is replaced with a structural map that has no silent drops.

System prompt is no longer a separate parameter on the Model trait. It is represented as a `Role::System` turn inside `ModelInput`, per the user's preference for "include system prompts" rather than treating system as a side channel.

